net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.input

Class ComponentInput

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.input.ComponentInput

  • public final class ComponentInput
extends Object
    Object to specify a primitive event. A primitive event does not really fit into the event/listener (signal/slot) model. It is meant as a means to call a method on a Component in which the process initiating the event knows what action has occured and directly modifies the Component. The Component itself should generate events to notify listeners that a change has occurred.
    Author:
    Pat B. Double (double@i2rd.com)
